Paul,<br><br>
Thanks! I decided to start at 1 all over again. Wishful thinking, though it is all in the attitude you have about yourself.<br><br>
It is my experience that people who choose to interfere in a destructive way in the lives of others usualy have no life themselves. They like to cause disruption and then feed off the emotional wreckage they cause. This is how they feel &quot;alive&quot;. I reality, all they are feeding is the bottomless pit within themselves, and nothing every works to fill it up.<br><br>
A friend once told me that insanity was doing the same thing over and over again, and expecting different results each time. Like the gambler who thinks the jackpot is just around the corner, only to find he has lost his shirt, once again, and the kids go hungry another night.<br><br>
Some of the people who disruptively post here are malevolent, mean spirited people, who are emotional vampires. Like Ed so aptly posted here a while back, these are people who are best viewed from a distance as to not contaminate ones self from their presence. The only purpose they serve is an example of what not to be like!<br><br>
Paul, thanks again! YES, I had too much pasta, but so what. HA! I find that enjoying life now is what life is all about, and not the &quot;dead zone&quot; in which too many of us 'Nam Vets find ourselves confined, through no fault of our own! <br><br>
